---
import PageShell from '../../components/PageShell.astro';
import CTABox from '../../components/CTABox.astro';
import ComparisonTable from '../../components/ComparisonTable.astro';

const tocItems = [
  { id: 'quick-verdict', title: 'Quick Verdict' },
  { id: 'comparison', title: 'Side-by-Side Comparison' },
  { id: 'cigna', title: 'Cigna Global' },
  { id: 'bupa', title: 'Bupa Global' },
  { id: 'allianz', title: 'Allianz Care' },
  { id: 'pricing', title: 'Pricing Comparison' },
  { id: 'oceania-details', title: 'Oceania Coverage Details' },
  { id: 'best-for', title: 'Best For' },
  { id: 'faqs', title: 'FAQs' },
];

const relatedLinks = [
  { href: '/providers/cigna-global', title: 'Cigna Global Full Review' },
  { href: '/providers/bupa-global', title: 'Bupa Global Full Review' },
  { href: '/providers/allianz-care', title: 'Allianz Care Full Review' },
  { href: '/countries/australia/insurance', title: 'Australia Expat Insurance' },
  { href: '/countries/new-zealand/insurance', title: 'New Zealand Expat Insurance' },
];

const mainComparisonColumns = ['Feature', 'Cigna Global', 'Bupa Global', 'Allianz Care'];
const mainComparisonRows = [
  ['Australia Network', 'Excellent', 'Very strong (local presence)', 'Good'],
  ['New Zealand Network', 'Good', 'Strong', 'Good'],
  ['Pacific Islands', 'Limited—evacuation focus', 'Limited—evacuation focus', 'Limited—evacuation focus'],
  ['Medical Evacuation', 'Included—all plans', 'Included—all plans', 'Included—all plans'],
  ['Local Office', 'Australia office', 'Australia (Bupa Australia)', 'Regional support'],
  ['Medicare Integration', 'Complements Medicare', 'Works alongside', 'Complements Medicare'],
  ['Direct Billing', 'Major hospitals', 'Extensive—local ties', 'Major hospitals'],
  ['Claims Processing', 'Fast—regional support', 'Fast—local processing', 'Standard'],
  ['Visa Compliance', 'Documentation provided', 'Documentation provided', 'Documentation provided'],
];

const pricingColumns = ['Coverage Level', 'Cigna Global', 'Bupa Global', 'Allianz Care'];
const pricingRows = [
  ['Core/Basic (inpatient)', '$3,000-4,200/yr', '$2,800-4,000/yr', '$2,600-3,800/yr'],
  ['Comprehensive/Gold', '$5,200-7,200/yr', '$5,000-6,800/yr', '$4,800-6,500/yr'],
  ['Premium/Platinum', '$7,200-9,500/yr', '$7,000-9,000/yr', '$6,800-8,800/yr'],
  ['Family coverage', '+75-95%', '+70-90%', '+65-85%'],
  ['Pacific Islands add-on', 'Included—with evacuation', 'Included—with evacuation', 'Included—with evacuation'],
];
---

<PageShell
  title="Cigna vs Bupa vs Allianz: Oceania & Pacific Insurance Comparison 2025"
  description="Compare Cigna, Bupa, and Allianz for expats in Australia, New Zealand, and the Pacific Islands. Networks, evacuation coverage, and local healthcare integration."
  headline="Cigna vs Bupa vs Allianz"
  subheadline="Which Provider is Best for Oceania & Pacific?"
  heroImage="/images/compare/oceania-pacific-hero.png"
  tocItems={tocItems}
  relatedLinks={relatedLinks}
>
  <section id="quick-verdict" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Quick Verdict</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-primary-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary-800 mb-3">Cigna Global</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">Best for comprehensive coverage with strong global benefits and mental health support for expats throughout the region.</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-primary-700">From $3,000/year</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-purple-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-purple-800 mb-3">Bupa Global</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">Best for Australia specifically, with strong local presence through Bupa Australia and extensive direct billing networks.</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-purple-700">From $2,800/year</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-green-800 mb-3">Allianz Care</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700 mb-4">Best value option with competitive pricing and solid coverage for expats prioritizing cost-effectiveness in the region.</p>
        <p class="text-sm font-medium text-green-700">From $2,600/year</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="comparison" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Side-by-Side Comparison</h2>
    <ComparisonTable columns={mainComparisonColumns} rows={mainComparisonRows} />
  </section>

  <section id="cigna" class="mb-12">
    <div class="bg-primary-50 rounded-lg p-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-primary-800 mb-4">Cigna Global</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-700 mb-6">Cigna Global provides comprehensive international health coverage across Oceania with particular strength in Australia. Their global infrastructure ensures consistent service whether you're in Sydney or a Pacific island.</p>
      
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Oceania Strengths</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
        <li>Regional office in Australia for local support</li>
        <li>Excellent hospital network in major Australian cities</li>
        <li>Strong mental health coverage—important for isolated postings</li>
        <li>Comprehensive evacuation coverage for Pacific Islands</li>
        <li>Works seamlessly with Australian Medicare for eligible expats</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Limitations</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
        <li>Premium pricing compared to regional competitors</li>
        <li>Pacific Islands coverage primarily evacuation-focused</li>
        <li>May be more coverage than needed if using public healthcare</li>
        <li>New Zealand network not as extensive as Australia</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="bupa" class="mb-12">
    <div class="bg-purple-50 rounded-lg p-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-purple-800 mb-4">Bupa Global</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-700 mb-6">Bupa has a significant local presence through Bupa Australia, giving them excellent hospital relationships and local market knowledge. This makes them particularly strong for expats settling in Australia long-term.</p>
      
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Oceania Strengths</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
        <li>Bupa Australia provides extensive local infrastructure</li>
        <li>Direct billing at most major Australian hospitals</li>
        <li>Fast local claims processing</li>
        <li>Good understanding of Australian healthcare landscape</li>
        <li>Strong network in New Zealand as well</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Limitations</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
        <li>Mental health coverage less comprehensive than Cigna</li>
        <li>Pacific Islands coverage limited to evacuation</li>
        <li>Local Bupa Australia plans are separate from Bupa Global</li>
        <li>International plan may overlap with local Medicare benefits</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="allianz" class="mb-12">
    <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-8">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-800 mb-4">Allianz Care</h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-neutral-700 mb-6">Allianz Care offers competitive pricing for Oceania coverage with solid benefits. A good choice for cost-conscious expats who want comprehensive coverage without premium pricing.</p>
      
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Oceania Strengths</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
        <li>Competitive pricing—typically 10-15% below premium competitors</li>
        <li>Good hospital networks in major Australian cities</li>
        <li>Flexible plan configurations</li>
        <li>High deductible options for cost savings</li>
        <li>Evacuation coverage for Pacific Islands included</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Limitations</h3>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
        <li>Less local presence than Bupa in Australia</li>
        <li>Mental health coverage varies by plan</li>
        <li>Claims processing may be slower than local competitors</li>
        <li>Network not as extensive in regional Australia</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </section>

  <CTABox
    title="Moving to Australia or the Pacific?"
    description="Get quotes for international health insurance that complements the Australian Medicare system or covers you across the Pacific region."
    buttonText="Compare Oceania Plans"
    buttonHref="/best/expat-health-insurance"
  />

  <section id="pricing" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Pricing Comparison</h2>
    <p class="text-neutral-600 mb-6">Estimated annual costs for a 35-year-old in Oceania. Australia tends to be more expensive than New Zealand due to higher healthcare costs.</p>
    <ComparisonTable columns={pricingColumns} rows={pricingRows} />
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 mt-4">Prices vary by specific country, age, coverage level, and deductible selection. Pacific Islands coverage focuses on evacuation to Australia or New Zealand.</p>
  </section>

  <section id="oceania-details" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Oceania Coverage Considerations</h2>
    
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Australia: Medicare and Private Insurance</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Many expats in Australia have access to Medicare through reciprocal healthcare agreements (for eligible countries) or permanent residency. International health insurance provides private hospital access, avoiding public waiting lists, and ensures continued coverage if you leave Australia. All three providers work alongside Medicare, covering gaps and providing private options.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">New Zealand Healthcare Access</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">New Zealand's public healthcare system is available to residents and some visa holders. Private insurance provides faster access to specialists and elective procedures. The private healthcare market is smaller than Australia's, but all three insurers have adequate networks in major cities.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Pacific Islands: Evacuation Essential</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Healthcare in Pacific island nations (Fiji, Samoa, Vanuatu, Papua New Guinea, etc.) is limited. For serious conditions, medical evacuation to Australia or New Zealand is standard practice. All three providers include evacuation coverage, but verify specific islands are covered and understand the evacuation protocols.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Remote Location Considerations</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Regional Australia and remote Pacific locations require robust evacuation coverage. Telemedicine is valuable when specialists are far away. Ensure your plan covers air ambulance and can coordinate complex evacuations. Cigna and Bupa have more experience with remote Australian location evacuations.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-3">Visa Insurance Requirements</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Some Australian visas require health insurance (student visas, certain work visas). International plans from these providers typically meet visa requirements—verify with immigration authorities. New Zealand also has insurance requirements for some visa categories. All three can provide documentation for visa applications.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="best-for" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Best For</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-primary-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-primary-800 mb-3">Choose Cigna If:</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>Mental health coverage is important</li>
          <li>You need coverage across multiple countries</li>
          <li>You want comprehensive benefits</li>
          <li>You're working in Pacific Islands</li>
          <li>You value global consistency</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-purple-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-purple-800 mb-3">Choose Bupa If:</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>You're settling in Australia long-term</li>
          <li>Direct billing convenience matters</li>
          <li>You want strong local support</li>
          <li>You prefer established local relationships</li>
          <li>Fast claims processing is important</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-green-50 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-green-800 mb-3">Choose Allianz If:</h3>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2 text-neutral-700">
          <li>Budget is a primary consideration</li>
          <li>You want competitive pricing</li>
          <li>High deductible plans appeal to you</li>
          <li>You're in major cities with good networks</li>
          <li>You want good value comprehensive coverage</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section id="faqs" class="mb-12">
    <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-neutral-800 mb-6">Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-2">Do I need international insurance if I have Australian Medicare?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Medicare provides public healthcare access, but waiting times for elective procedures can be long. International insurance gives you private hospital choice, shorter wait times, and continued coverage if you travel or relocate. It's valuable as a top-up even with Medicare access.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-2">What happens if I need medical care in a Pacific Island?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">For minor issues, local care may be adequate. For serious conditions, your insurer will arrange evacuation to the nearest appropriate facility—typically Australia or New Zealand. Contact your insurer's assistance line immediately for any serious health concerns in the Pacific.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-2">Is Bupa Global the same as Bupa Australia?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">No, they're related but separate products. Bupa Australia sells local Australian health insurance. Bupa Global is international coverage for people living outside their home country. The connection does provide better local networks for Bupa Global members in Australia.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-2">Will my plan cover me in regional Australia?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">Yes, all three cover regional Australia. Network hospitals may be further away, so evacuation to major cities may be needed for complex care. Verify network coverage in your specific region. Telemedicine helps bridge gaps when specialists aren't locally available.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-2">What about coverage in Papua New Guinea?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">PNG has limited healthcare infrastructure. All three providers focus on evacuation to Australia for serious cases. Some local hospitals in Port Moresby may have direct billing arrangements. For anything serious, expect evacuation. Mining and resources expats in PNG typically have robust evacuation coverage.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white border border-neutral-200 rounded-lg p-6">
        <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-800 mb-2">Do I need specific coverage for adventure activities in New Zealand?</h3>
        <p class="text-neutral-700">New Zealand's ACC (Accident Compensation Corporation) covers accidents for everyone in NZ, including tourists. International insurance provides additional coverage and repatriation. Adventure activities like bungee jumping and skiing are typically covered by these plans, but verify extreme activities.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="bg-neutral-100 rounded-lg p-6 mb-12">
    <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600">
      <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> Healthcare systems and insurance requirements vary across Oceania. This comparison is for informational purposes only. Verify current coverage details, network availability, and visa requirements directly with providers and relevant authorities. Pacific Islands coverage may have specific limitations—confirm coverage for your specific destination.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageShell>
